Early class III protraction facemask treatment reduces the need for orthognathic surgery from two-thirds (CG) to one-third (PFG);

Early protraction facemask treatment-related improvements in SNA, SNB and ANB were not maintained at 6 years follow-up. However, there was a statistically significant long-term clockwise rotation in the maxilla and mandible in the PFG;

Sixty eight per cent of patient in the PFG presented with a positive overjet at age 15 years and

Early protraction facemask treatment does not seem to confer a clinically significant psychosocial benefit.
